Ghana’s Main Cocoa Crop Rises to a Record 904,000 Tons, Reuters Reports

-- B y   A n t o n y   S g u a z z i n
-- 
2011-05-30T08:38:09Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-30/ghana-s-main-cocoa-crop-rises-to-a-record-904-000-tons-reuters-reports.html
Ghana ’s main cocoa crop has risen to
a record 904,000 metric tons and it expects a second “light”
crop of at least 80,000 tons, Reuters reported, citing Tony
Fofie, the head of Ghana’s Cocoa Board.  The country’s previous full season record was 740,000 tons
in the 2005-2006 season, Reuters reported.  Click here for web link  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
